SYSTEM HEALTH COMMANDS 
**************************************
1.command : uptime
    >it display the how long the system is running and number of users logged in,and shows the load average

2.command : top
 shows the real time system performance
 .cpu usage
 .memory usage 
 .running processor
 .system load

3.command : free -h
 it shows the meomory usage and swap meamory in readable formate

4.command : df -h
 it shows the disk space and storage health

 check the specific directory
 command :df -h /var

5.command : lscpu
 it display the cpu details like:core,architecture,speed,threads

6.command :ps -ef
 it shows the all running process in the system ,it shows the systemv format
 and it is process structure 

7.command :vmstat 
 it shows the virtual machine statics

 vmstat 1 5
 it shows the statics 5 times per second

8.command :iostat   
 it shows the disk performance
 -disk bottle necks
 -slow performances issues

 command not found :yum install sysstat -y

 command:iostat -x 1 3
 i shows the disk performance 1 second 3 times

9.command :sar
 it shows the hostorical data
 cpu usage
 memory usage
 network stats

 command :sar -u 1 3
 -u is cpu utilization
 1 second per 3 times

10.command :dmesg
 it shows the kernel system messages

>to check the system errors,debug the hardware issues and see the boot messages,identify the network and disk problems

 commands :dmesg | grep -i errors
           dmesg | grep -i disk
           dmesg | tail -20
           dmesg | grep -i usb

11.command :journalctl
 it shows the complete system logs
 >service failure
 >login issues
 >system errors

 command :journalctl -xe |tail -20

12.command :ps -aux 
 it is simillar to the ps -ef command but here ps -aux is a BSD format
 it is a resource usage

 find the top cpu process
 command : ps aux --sort=-%cpu | head

 find the top memory process
 command : ps aux --sort=-%mem | head

13.command :free -m
 it is shows the memory usage in megabytes 

14.command :who
 who command shows the current user login and user details
  tty = local login
  pts = remote login

15.command : last
 last is used to check the login history for the userd ,logedout time and source ip for security auditing

 command : last | head -10
           last -5
           lastb

16.command : du -h
 it shows the folder size 

command : du -sh
          du -sh *


          





